<html xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_4.xsd">
<!-- We need a doctype to allow us to use special characters like &nbsp; 
	 We use a "strict" DTD to make IE follow the alignment rules. -->

<body class="container">
	<h3>Output</h3>

	The general pattern for output in Tapestry is this: the class exposes named properties (ie. public getters), 
	eg. <code>getMessage()</code>, and the template references them, eg. <code><![CDATA[${message}]]></code>.
	The reference <code><![CDATA[${message}]]></code> is called an <em>expansion</em>.

	<div class="eg">
		${message}
	</div>

